Question 29 
[Steel Structures : General Design Requirements]
The elements that DO NOT increase the strength of structural steel are
(A) Carbon 
(B) Manganese
(C) Sulphur 
(D) Chlorine 
Ans. (C,D)
explanation_text:
Sol. 
Chlorine and Sulphur do not increase the strength of structural steel.
Hence, the correct options are (C) and (D).
